# The Holodeck: Phong Shader Simulator

## Manipulating Shaders in Real Time

This interactive simulator demonstrates the **Phong reflection model**, a mathematical lighting model developed by Bui Tuong Phong in 1973. It is one of the most fundamental algorithms in computer graphics, bridging the gap between flat shading and photorealistic rendering.

Use the sliders on the right to adjust how different light properties affect the material surface of the sphere.

