## Technical Details

The Phong reflection model computes the color of a point on a 3D surface as a combination of three distinct components:

1. **Ambient Lighting**: Represents uniform background light scattered throughout the environment. It ensures that parts of the object not directly hit by the light source do not appear completely black.
2. **Diffuse Lighting**: Represents light reflected equally in all directions from the surface. The intensity depends on the angle between the light source and the surface normal (Lambertian reflection).
3. **Specular Lighting**: Creates bright highlights (shininess) on glossy surfaces. It is view-dependent and relies on the reflection direction of the light vector relative to the camera viewpoint.
